\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. C. vitalba }L.,{\i  loc. cit.} (1753). Deciduous, woody climber up to 30 m. Leaves 1-pinnate; leaflets ovate, rarely linear-lanceolate, dentate or subentire. Flowers c. 2 cm in diameter, fragrant. Perianth-segments obtuse, greenish-white, pubescent on both surfaces. Anthers 1-2 mm. Receptacle pubescent. Achenes scarcely compressed. 2n = 16.{\i   S.,W. & C. Europe.} Al Au Be Br Bu Co Cz Ga Ge Gr He Ho Hs Hu It Ju Lu Rm Rs(W, K) Sa Si Tu [Da Hb Po Su].
