\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. C. orientalis }L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 543 (1753). Like {\b 2} but leaflets oblong or linear, 3-lobed, often dentate, glaucous; perianth-segments acuminate, yellowish. Stamens ciliate.{\i  S.E. Russia and Ukraine; naturalized locally elsewhere.} Rs(*W, E) [Cz Hs It]. ({\i Temperate Asia.})
\par 

