\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. C. recta }L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 544 (1753) ({\i C. lathyrifolia} Besser). Erect herb with fistular stems 1-1·5 m. Leaves up to 25 cm, 1-pinnate; leaflets 5-9 cm, ovate, acute, usually entire, stalked. Flowers c. 2 cm in diameter, white, erect, fragrant. Perianth-segments 0·5-1·8 cm, with tomentose margins but otherwise glabrous.{\i  C., S. & E. Europe, northwards to} 57° 30'{\i  N. in C. Russia and westwards to N. Spain}. Au Bu Co Cz Ga Ge He Hs Hu It Ju Po Rm Rs(*B, C, W, K, E) [Be]
